&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Career Team is a leading workforce development organization on a mission to transform lives.&amp;nbsp; We blend cutting-edge technology with compassionate, high-touch services to drive real, measurable outcomes in the lives of job seekers across the country.&amp;nbsp; At Career Team, we’re solving today’s unemployment challenges with smart software, world-class trainers, dedicated case managers, dynamic job developers, and innovative partners. If you&#39;re passionate about making a difference and believe in the power of technology to transform lives, you’ll feel right at home here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Accounting Supervisor is responsible for all financial activities across multiple projects and leads the day-to-day operations of the accounting team. The primary responsibilities for this role focus on overseeing invoicing, analyzing, and reporting project financial status for various projects across our continuously expanding organization. The ideal candidate must have the ability to interact with co-workers and customers at all levels. An ideal candidate would thrive in a fast-paced environment while remaining flexible, proactive, resourceful, and efficient. The Accounting Supervisor must be able to maintain a high-level of accuracy and confidentiality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position reports directly to the Director of Finance, is remote, and will work PST business hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Supervisory &amp;amp; Strategic Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Supervise, mentor, and train accounting staff; manage workload distribution to ensure all departmental deadlines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Review &amp;amp; Approval:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform first-level review of journal entries, reconciliations, and financial statements prepared by staff to ensure accuracy and GAAP compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify, develop, and implement streamlined accounting procedures and internal controls to enhance department efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance Oversight:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure the team follows procedures and policies to facilitate effective financial reporting and compliance with Federal WIOA, local, State, and corporate policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fiscal Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Direct fiscal operations relating to financial planning, funds management, accounting, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budgeting &amp;amp; Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the preparation and maintenance of project budgets, forecasts, and working capital requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Liaison:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as a primary point of contact for senior leadership, Executive Directors and our contracts/customers, providing high-level financial insight and performance reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Operational Duties&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy Compliance &amp;amp; WIOA Stewardship:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure that projects fulfill all financial obligations in a timely and economic manner in accordance with established policies and WIOA guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contractual &amp;amp; Project Coordination:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate accounting activities for assigned projects, including the establishment and monitoring of contract-specific procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disbursement &amp;amp; Payroll Oversight:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee the processing of employee expenses, participant expenses, vendor project invoices, and program payroll analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
